-- Luxottica Said to Plan Meet Bond Investor Meetings in Europe
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-03-02T13:56:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/luxottica-said-to-plan-meet-bond-investor-meetings-in-europe.html
Luxottica Group SpA (LUX)  plans to meet
bond investors in Europe starting March 6, according to a banker
with knowledge of the arrangements.  Bank of America Corp., Credit Agricole CIB, Citigroup Inc.,
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc and  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  are
organizing the presentations, the banker said. The company may
sell bonds in euros after the meetings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  